title: For Sale:  Kimber Ultra Bel Air II, Special Edition
postcontent:
Kimber Ultra Bel Air II, Special Edition
 NEW IN BOX
 The Kimber Bel Air Ultra II is a 3" barrel 9mm 1911 paired with a compact frame. The stainless steel slide wears a beautiful mirror polished finish. Kimber workmanship and quality are easy to see, even down to the smallest detail. The melded forged stainless steel slide and lightweight aluminum alloy frame fit together with tight tolerances and function perfectly.
Recoil on the Kimber Bel Air Ultra II feels significantly less than that of competing designs. This is due in part to this pistol's lower center of gravity, which is slightly below the slide, and very close to where the shooter's hand grips the gun. Although the single-stack magazine puts the Kimber's capacity at only eight rounds, the relatively small diameter of the 1911's frame still allow the shooter to create a secure two-handed grip.
A match grade barrel and bushing deliver tack driving accuracy. For added reliability, Kimber includes a full- length guide rod, as the shorter G.I. style guide rods have a tendency to bind or break over time. Snag-free, low profile sights sit on top of the slide and provide a consistent target presentation.
The checkering on the mainspring housing, along with the texture of the ivory Micarta thin grips feels secure.The knurled extended magazine release of the Kimber Bel Air Ultra II is a huge improvement over releases seen on other pistols. Performing tactical reloads is quick, simple and efficient.
The Kimber Bel Air Ultra II single stage, match grade aluminum trigger is a joy to pull, especially over the mushy triggers seen on most double action pistols. The 4 to 5lbs pull is steady and smooth, while the reset is short and crisp. This is a gun that fires naturally, even for beginner's that have "low and left" trigger slap tendencies. In fact, the Kimber Bel Air Ultra II has one of the smoothest trigger pulls of any production 1911 on the market.
Other features include a clean, single sided thumb safety. Many shooters actually prefer this style over the bulkier ambidextrous paddles. To further minimize felt recoil, the grip safety is a high-ride designed beavertail that quickly establishes a positive grip for maximum control in stress fire situations.

title: For Sale:  1911A1 pistol, Remington, Dulith finish
postcontent: Early, Dulith finish. Serial # 971,896 with NO prefix rather than an underlined No. Although some publications list this serial number as March 1943 production, it may have been finished after production was started again in May-June ’43 (after shutdown in Feb.) with the new on site Ordnance inspector. He designated that new production pistols would have the NO prefix to distinguish newly produced pistols. Since old receivers were used up in new production a mix of NO and No can be found in serial number range 955,000 to 1,016,000. This pistol has the Du-lite finish with some blued parts. Regulations required the same finish on the receiver and slide but parts could be other finishes. Slide is type 2 with markings 1 3/8” long and ending in N.Y.U.S.A. Type 2 slides started about #935,000. Blued High Standard barrel. P stamped on the left side of the lug, HS on the right. Bore is mirror with a little micro erosion from firing. Feed ramp is bright with traces of finish, not polished. Recoil spring plug is blued. Remington narrow hammer. Finely checkered early Remington mainspring cover. Blued checkered slide stop (Colt). Blued safety checkered on top and bottom with no undercut (Colt). Colt supplied these parts to Remington until Remington could make them. Front sight has sloped serrated ramp on rear. Rounded cut on front of rear sight with squared aperture. Early Keyes grips without re-enforcing rings around screws. No hits, bangs or smashed checkering. Bluing on pistol is about 95%. There is some wear on the top of the barrel and on other moving parts. Du-lite was not as sturdy as Parkerizing. Heat treated area on end of the slide is very visible but there is none above the slide stop.
